               <p>JOHN BAPTIST. I lodge in <placeName id="t18310630-207-crimeloc1088">Cornwall-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-207-crimeloc1088" type="placeName" value="Cornwall-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-207-crimeloc1088" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-207-off1086 t18310630-207-crimeloc1088"></join>. The prisoner lodged in the same room; I had a watch in my chest- one Friday, about a month ago, the prisoner slept in my room, and had been there that day; I saw the watch at Mr. Phillips' shop - it had a chain and two seals to it; the prisoner is a countryman of mine.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-207-person1551">
                  WATKIN 
                  PHILLIPS
               <interp inst="t18310630-207-person1551" type="surname" value="PHILLIPS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-207-person1551" type="given" value="WATKIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-207-person1551" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I deal in clothes. I bought this watch of the prisoner; he came one Friday with it - I laid the watch in my window, and the prosecutor saw it and claimed it - the prisoner said he was going away and the watch was of no use to him; he asked 13s. for it - I offered him 9s.; he went away, returned, and took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-207-person1552">
